{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Device Memory API","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_Memory_API","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.Navigator.deviceMemory","api.WorkerNavigator.deviceMemory","http.headers.Device-Memory"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_Memory_API\" aria-current=\"page\">Device Memory API</a></em></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/deviceMemory\"><code>Navigator.deviceMemory</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WorkerNavigator/deviceMemory\"><code>WorkerNavigator.deviceMemory</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"DefaultAPISidebar","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div><div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> This feature is available in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Workers_API\">Web Workers</a></p>\n</div>\n<p>The capabilities of a client device largely depend on the amount of available RAM. Traditionally, developers had to use heuristics and either benchmark a device or infer device capabilities based on other factors like the device manufacturer or User Agent strings.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"determining_device_memory","title":"Determining device memory","isH3":false,"content":"<p>There are two ways to determine the approximate amount of RAM a device has: use the Device Memory JavaScript API or accept Client Hints.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"javascript_api","title":"JavaScript API","isH3":true,"content":"<p>You may query the approximate amount of RAM a device has by retrieving <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/deviceMemory\"><code>Navigator.deviceMemory</code></a> or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WorkerNavigator/deviceMemory\"><code>WorkerNavigator.deviceMemory</code></a>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token constant\">RAM</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>deviceMemory<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"client_hints","title":"Client Hints","isH3":true,"content":"<p>You may also use the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Client_hints\">Client Hints</a> HTTP Header with the <code>Device-Memory</code> directive to retrieve the same approximate RAM capacity.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"interfaces","title":"Interfaces","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"extensions_to_other_interfaces","title":"Extensions to other interfaces","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"navigator.devicememory\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/deviceMemory\"><code>Navigator.deviceMemory</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the approximate amount of device memory in gigabytes.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"workernavigator.devicememory\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WorkerNavigator/deviceMemory\"><code>WorkerNavigator.deviceMemory</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the approximate amount of device memory in gigabytes.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://www.w3.org/TR/device-memory/","title":"Device Memory"}],"query":"api.Navigator.deviceMemory,api.WorkerNavigator.deviceMemory,http.headers.Device-Memory"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"browser_compatibility","title":"Browser compatibility","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"api.Navigator.deviceMemory","id":"api.Navigator.deviceMemory","isH3":true,"query":"api.Navigator.deviceMemory"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"api.WorkerNavigator.deviceMemory","id":"api.WorkerNavigator.deviceMemory","isH3":true,"query":"api.WorkerNavigator.deviceMemory"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"http.headers.Device-Memory","id":"http.headers.Device-Memory","isH3":true,"query":"http.headers.Device-Memory"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Device-Memory\"><code>Device-Memory</code></a> header</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Determining device memory","id":"determining_device_memory"},{"text":"Interfaces","id":"interfaces"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The capabilities of a client device largely depend on the amount of available RAM. Traditionally, developers had to use heuristics and either benchmark a device or infer device capabilities based on other factors like the device manufacturer or User Agent strings.","popularity":0.0008,"modified":"2023-11-29T13:41:35.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/device_memory_api","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/device_memory_api/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/ca577adc00ddc882765c131739ad2ed25edd2285","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"Device Memory API","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_Memory_API","title":"Device Memory API"}],"pageTitle":"Device Memory API - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}